{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"beaee191-804f-4856-a7e3-45eaed0848ba","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory, and no dump analysis tools are installed. Here's how to proceed:\n\n**1. Upload the dump file** to this directory so I can work with it.\n\n**2. Once uploaded, I can install `dotnet-dump` and analyze it:**\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\n**Key commands inside `dotnet-dump analyze`:**\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` | Inspect specific threads |\n\n**If you'd rather analyze it locally**, run:\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nThen start with `pe` to print the exception and `clrstack` to see the stack trace at the time of the crash.\n\nWould you like to upload the dump file here, or do you need help interpreting specific output from your local analysis?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"37c8a686-ff9b-4696-8b96-4ca250d075c1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There's no .dmp file in the current directory and no dump analysis tools installed. Let me provide guidance on how to analyze a .NET crash dump.","outputTokens":345,"requestId":"6404:C174F:1520DFC:18AB1E7:69EC1B01"},"id":"706effe0-2ab4-43c1-bd20-74ad3bae0808","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:38:18.346Z","parentId":"bf414ea1-70c1-4306-ae3b-45e57a922cea"}
